    • Method Detail

      • read

        public long read(ExtractorInput input)
          throws java.io.IOException,
                 java.lang.InterruptedException
        Description copied from interface: OggSeeker
        Reads data from the ExtractorInput to build the SeekMap or to continue a progressive seek.

        If more data is required or if the position of the input needs to be modified then a position from which data should be provided is returned. Else a negative value is returned. If a seek has been completed then the value returned is -(currentGranule + 2). Else it is -1.

        Specified by:
        read in interface OggSeeker
        Parameters:
        input - The ExtractorInput to read from.
        Returns:
        A non-negative position to seek the ExtractorInput to, or -(currentGranule + 2) if the progressive seek has completed, or -1 otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If reading from the ExtractorInput fails.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted.

      • getNextSeekPosition

        public long getNextSeekPosition(long targetGranule,
                                ExtractorInput input)
                         throws java.io.IOException,
                                java.lang.InterruptedException
        Returns a position converging to the targetGranule to which the ExtractorInput has to seek and then be passed for another call until a negative number is returned. If a negative number is returned the input is at a position which is before the target page and at which it is sensible to just skip pages to the target granule and pre-roll instead of doing another seek request.
        Parameters:
        targetGranule - the target granule position to seek to.
        input - the ExtractorInput to read from.
        Returns:
        the position to seek the ExtractorInput to for a next call or -(currentGranule + 2) if it's close enough to skip to the target page.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown if reading from the input fails.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - thrown if interrupted while reading from the input.

      • skipToPageOfGranule

        long skipToPageOfGranule(ExtractorInput input,
                         long targetGranule,
                         long currentGranule)
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         java.lang.InterruptedException
        Skips to the position of the start of the page containing the targetGranule and returns the granule of the page previous to the target page.
        Parameters:
        input - the ExtractorInput to read from.
        targetGranule - the target granule.
        currentGranule - the current granule or -1 if it's unknown.
        Returns:
        the granule of the prior page or the currentGranule if there isn't a prior page.
        Throws:
        ParserException - thrown if populating the page header fails.
        java.io.IOException - thrown if reading from the input fails.
        java.lang.InterruptedException - thrown if interrupted while reading from the input.
